	<topic>LG_LOGIN Dialog Component
</topic>
<description>Provides a method to login to the application.</description>	


<sections>
<section>
	<description>The LG_LOGIN login component provides a method to login to the application. The security configuration allows password change and recovery, so the component shows views for those options. The LG_LOGIN component Login view:
</description>
<figure><link>images/ASW_lg_login.gif</link></figure>	
	
	
</section>	
<section>
	<description>The LG_LOGIN component Change Password view 
</description>
	<figure><link>images/ASW_lg_login_2.gif</link></figure>	
</section>
<section>
	<description>The LG_LOGIN component Lost Info view 
</description>
	<figure><link>images/ASW_lg_login_3.gif</link></figure>	
</section>


<section>
	<description>The LG_LOGIN dialog component contains three views to show during login. Each view can have its own layout and stylesheet. The Login view is a freeform layout based on a tabular layout. The other views are also tabular. 
The options and views shown in the builder are determined by the security settings. Some options are not shown because the settings do not permit them. 
</description>
	
	
</section>
<section>
	<title>Containers
</title>
	<description>LOGIN.A5W
</description>
	
</section>	
	

<section>
<title>Notable Login View Layout Settings</title>	
	<cases>
		<case>
			<title>Layout Options > Style name </title>
			<description>Set to "shopcart". </description>
		</case>
		<case>
			<title>Layout Options > Show Remember me?</title>
			<description>Set to TRUE. </description>
		</case>
		<case>
			<title>Layout Options > Show Options </title>
			<description>Set to "Show as Links". </description>
		</case>
		<case>
			<title>Layout Options > Freeform Layout </title>
			<description>Set to TRUE. </description>
		</case>
		<case>
			<title>Layout Options > Freeform Template </title>
			<description>Change to " 
Email Address
{Userid}
Password
{Password}
{SubmitButton} {ResetButton}
{RememberMe}
{ChgPasswordLink} {LostPasswordLink}
" </description>
		</case>
		
		
	</cases>
	
	
	
</section>

